Object.Field: LKM Hyperion Essbase METADATA to SQL

Author: Oracle Version: 9.3.1.1 Last update: Sept 18th 2007
Description: - This is a load knowledge module that extracts hyperion essbase metadata and loads to the staging area.

The selection criteria based upon which the members from the hierarchy should be extracted.
The supported selection member selection criteria are - IDescendants - Descendants - IChildren - Children - Member_Only - Level0 - UDA

The member name for applying the specified filter criteria. If no member is specified then the filter criteria is applied on the root member.
NOTE: If the MEMBER_FILTER_CRITERIA is UDA, then the MEMBER_FILTER_VALUE should be the UDA values based on which filtering should be done.
Flag to indicate if logging should be performed during the load process. If set to Yes, logging would be done to the file specified by the LOG_FILE_NAME option.
The fully qualified name of the file into which logging is to be done
The maximum number of allowed error

By default, this value is zero, which means that it will ignore any errors that occurs during the extract and load process into the staging area table. If this is set to a value greater than zero, then, the extract process that loads into the staging table will stop with an error once it reaches the specified number of errors.
If this option is set to "Yes", error records are logged to a file specified by the ERROR_LOG_FILE name option.
If this option is set to "Yes", error records are logged to a file specified by the ERROR_LOG_FILE name option.
The location of the error log file
Specify the name of the file into which the error records should be logged.
Specify the name of the file into which the error records should be logged.
The column delimiter for error file
The column delimiter to be used for the error records file.
The row delimiter for error file
The row delimiter to be used for the error records file.
The text delimiter for error file

The text delimiter to be used for the column data in the error records file. For e.g, if the text delimiter is set as ' " ' (double quote), then all the columns in the error records file will be delimited by double quotes.
Flag to log the header row
If this option is set to Yes, then the header row containing the column names is logged to the error records file.
Set this option to NO if you wish to retain temporary objects (tables, files and scripts) after integration. Useful for debugging.
Enter alias table, leave blank for default.

from java.util import HashMap from java.util import Map from java.lang import Boolean from java.lang import Integer from com.hyperion.odi.common import ODIConstants from com.hyperion.odi.connection import HypAppConnectionFactory
# # Source Essbase Application connection properties #
serverName = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_DSERV_NAME")%>" userName = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_USER_NAME")%>" password = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_PASS")%>" application = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_CATALOG")%>" database = "<%=odiRef.getInfo("SRC_SCHEMA")%>"
portStr = "1423" srvportParts = serverName.split(':',2) srvStr = srvportParts[0]
if(len(srvportParts) > 1): portStr = srvportParts[1]
# # Put the connection properites and initialize the essbase App Reader # srcProps = HashMap() srcProps.put(ODIConstants.SERVER,srvStr) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.PORT, portStr) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.USER,userName) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.PASSWORD,password) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.APPLICATION_NAME,application) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.DATABASE_NAME,database) srcProps.put(ODIConstants.READER_TYPE,"METADATA_READER")
print "Initalizing the Essbase App Reader and connecting" essbaseAppReader = HypAppConnectionFactory.getAppReader(HypAppConnectionFactory.APP_ESSBASE, srcProps);
# # Get the connection properties for the staging database # connection = odiRef.getJDBCConnection("DEST") stagingTableName = '<%=odiRef.getTable("L", "COLL_NAME", "W")%>' stagCols = '<%=odiRef.getColList("", "[CX_COL_NAME]=[COL_NAME] ", ", ", "", "")%>'
print "Staging Columns %s" % stagCols
# #extract the LKM Options # alias_table = "<%=odiRef.getOption("ALIAS_TABLE")%>" logEnabled = <%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_ENABLED")%> logFileName = r"<%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_FILE_NAME")%>" memberFilterCriteria = "<%=odiRef.getOption("MEMBER_FILTER_CRITERIA")%>" memberFilterValue = "<%=odiRef.getOption("MEMBER_FILTER_VALUE")%>".decode('utf-8') maxErrors = <%=odiRef.getOption("MAXIMUM_ERRORS_ALLOWED")%> logErrors = <%=odiRef.getOption("LOG_ERRORS")%> errFileName = r"<%=odiRef.getOption("ERROR_LOG_FILENAME")%>" errColDelimiter = r"<%=odiRef.getOption("ERR_COL_DELIMITER")%>" errRowDelimiter = r"<%=odiRef.getOption("ERR_ROW_DELIMITER")%>" errTextDelimiter = r"<%=odiRef.getOption("ERR_TEXT_DELIMITER")%>" logHeader = <%=odiRef.getOption("ERR_LOG_HEADER_ROW")%> dimension = "<%=odiRef.getFrom()%>"
print "Dimension Name is %s " % dimension
#set the extract options extractOptions = HashMap()
#generic ODI Knowledge module options extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_ENABLED, Boolean(logEnabled)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_FILE_NAME, logFileName) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.DATABASE_CONNECTION, connection) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.MAPPED_COLUMN_NAMES, stagCols) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.STAGING_TABLE_NAME,stagingTableName) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.MAXIMUM_ERRORS_ALLOWED, Integer(maxErrors)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.LOG_ERRORS, Boolean(logErrors)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERROR_LOG_FILENAME, errFileName) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_COL_DELIMITER, errColDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_ROW_DELIMITER, errRowDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_TEXT_DELIMITER, errTextDelimiter) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ERR_LOG_HEADER_ROW, Boolean(logHeader)) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.ALIAS_TABLE, alias_table)
#essbase specified load options extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.MEMBER_FILTER_CRITERIA, memberFilterCriteria) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.MEMBER_FILTER_VALUE, memberFilterValue) extractOptions.put(ODIConstants.DIMENSION, dimension)
essbaseAppReader.beginExtract(extractOptions)
statString = stats.toString() raise OdiKMException("ODIKM-ESSBASE-11004", "ODIKM-ESSBASE-11004: Essbase Metadata Extract Summary",[statString])
